The Lagos State Judicial Panel of Inquiry and Restitution (LSJPIR) has urged general public to come forward with their various petitions bordering on police/security agent brutality and extra-judicial killings. The panel  was recently set up by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu  to look into the grievances of the victims of Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS) related abuses and Lekki Toll Gate incident Chairperson of the panel, Justice Doris Okuwobi (retd) on Monday disclosed  that the panel has so far received 15 petitions from abuse victims. Justice Okuwobi said the panel is independent of the state government and would  ensured that individuals with valid complaints of human rights violations will receive immediate compensation. 